How to change system font for a more goodlooking one:

It affects at font on the i3bar, on the titles, on all gtk apps, etc

1. Download a font, for example: https://github.com/supermarin/YosemiteSanFranciscoFont
2. Go to Manual Install -> downlad the zipped font files
3. unzip it
4. cd new_folder
5. cp *.ttf ~/.fonts

6. Go to config file, and type that to configure i3 fonts: 
    font pango:System San Francisco Display 10
7. Do that to config gtk fonts:
    7.1. Install 'lxappearance'
    7.2. Force to create a config file by changing to a random font and save it
    7.3. Go to ~/.gtkrc-2.0 and change the font
    7.4. Go to ~/.config/gtk-3.0/settings.ini and change the font

